reviewText: I watched this with my daughter and it was good but it was predictable and my daughter knew what was gonna happen next. Overall I liked it.
I bought the movie for my girlfriend b/c she loves Lance Gross. Didn't know what I would get with the movie. It turned out to be better than we both thought!

One of the most heartfelt movies I've seen in a long time!

Very good acting, credible characters, no CARICATURES, or false notes, or buffoonery or vulgarity

A very touching, very believable, gives-you-hope-for-black-love, black love story

I highly recommend it!

This film is inspirational, uplifting, thought provoking, and hilarious! The thing that I appreciate the most is that it's not stereotypical and therefore predictable! I didn't want it to end! Furthermore, I absolutely love how you see people of color represented in such a positive light! I encourage everyone, all races, creeds, cultures, young and old, to watch this heart-warming film! Definitely want to see more movies from Lance Gross

"The Last Fall" could have been a good film, but it falls short in two major categories, the lead actor Lance Gross is not a strong dramatic lead, and the storyline is predictable, especially with the way the film concludes. The film shows that Lance Gross has a lot of shortcomings when it comes to pulling off truly poignant and impactful sceens that need to pull the audiences into the film and make them invested in the characters. A stronger and more resonant lead actor would have given them film a valiant and more noble push beyond the normal realm of mediocre sports dramas.
A good famly movie to share with everyone you know. A wholesome relateable story. This is exellent for young people,to prepare for the future and obtain your education.
Wonderfully developed characters and great dialogue. I really enjoyed this film and identified with the characters. Well written, well shot. Well done.

Gross and Beharie have great on-screen chemistry.  The storyline may be a bit predictable, but what is not, is the sincerity of Gross' character. I only wish the movie was longer.  Beautiful romance!  Great casting!  Quality film!

Surprisingly NICE love story woven in a storyline of disappointments, life choices, finding happiness, dealing with family bridges, and forgiveness. If you are searching for an uplifting movies without a lot of violence or cursing (brief love scene)...you'll enjoy this film.  I watched with my husband...I'm not into football but we did discuss some of the points about football's player image & pay...interesting how easily it is to assume how others are living the "big" life.  I enjoyed the cast...Lance Gross played his part well...as well, as the rest of the cast! Good to see a loving Black parents & family on one hand. On the other hand the efforts made to strive to start showing the love felt in a family. Good to see positivity and balance in a quote unquote "Black movie" this is a movie that can be enjoy by all races if given a chance.
This was a really good movie. Lance Gross is a very good lead actor in this movie. The chemistry (romance) between him and Nicole Beharie in this movie was believable and true.
Pretty good better than what I thought it was going to be.
